      "question": "If a card is drawn from a well-shuffled deck of $52$ cards, the probability that the card drawn is not a face card is:",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Identify the total number of cards in a deck, which is $52$.",
          "Identify the number of face cards (King, Queen, Jack of each suit). There are $3 \times 4 = 12$ face cards.",
          "Calculate the probability of drawing a face card: $P(\text{Face Card}) = \\frac{12}{52} = \\frac{3}{13}$.",
          "Use the property of complementary events: $P(\text{not a face card}) = 1 - P(\text{Face Card})$.",
          "Calculate: $1 - \\frac{3}{13} = \\frac{13-3}{13} = \\frac{10}{13}$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$P(\text{Face Card}) = \\frac{12}{52} = \\frac{3}{13} \\ P(\text{not Face Card}) = 1 - P(\text{Face Card}) \\ P(\text{not Face Card}) = 1 - \\frac{3}{13} = \\frac{10}{13}$"
      },
